Our Purposes for Collecting and Using Personal Information
The categories of Personal Information listed above may be used for the purposes disclosed in this Privacy Policy including to provide services requested, managing accounts including registration and participation in products and services; maintaining and improving Pure Flix sites, products and services; identity resolution, personalizing customer experiences including tailoring content; consumer marketing including push notifications, online and mobile ads, emails, and SMS/text messaging from Pure Flix; to maintain security on Pure Flix properties and conduct security screenings to the extent permitted by law; and to satisfy compliance and legal obligations.
Pure Flix may have collected any of the above categories of Personal Information and Sensitive Personal Information about California residents during the past 12 months for the purposes described in this policy.
Sources From Which We Collect Personal Information
We collect the categories of Personal Information listed above from the following categories of sources: consumers, data analytics companies, ad networks, social networks, internet service providers, service providers that help us to run our business, and data resellers such as data management platforms. We also collect Personal Information automatically via Tracking Technologies when you use our websites or mobile apps.
How We Disclose Personal Information
We may disclose any of the categories of Personal Information listed above with service providers that perform services on our behalf, including communications, processing payments, supporting our websites and mobile apps, storing data, providing analytics, supporting our marketing and advertising, or otherwise helping us to operate our business.
Pure Flix does not sell or share consumers’ Personal Information in exchange for money; however, Pure Flix shares the categories of Personal Information with third parties and service providers to deliver more meaningful ads and other communications to consumers, and for other similar reasons provided in this Policy. Some of these uses of Personal Information may be considered “sales” or “sharing” for cross-context behavioral advertising under the CCPA. We may sell/share each of the categories of Personal Information listed above with third parties such as advertising networks, internet service providers, data analytics providers, operating systems and platforms, and social networks.
Pure Flix does not have actual knowledge that it sells the Personal Information of California residents under 16 years of age without affirmative authorization.
How Long We Keep Your Personal Information
We keep the categories of Personal Information described above for as long as necessary or permitted for the purposes described in this Notice or otherwise authorized by law. This generally means holding the information for as long as one of the following apply:
Your Personal Information is reasonably necessary to manage our operations, to manage your relationship with us, or to satisfy another purpose for which we collected the information;
Your Personal Information is reasonably necessary to carry out a disclosed purpose that is reasonably compatible with the context in which the Personal Information was collected;
The Personal Information is reasonably necessary to protect or defend our rights or property (which will generally relate to applicable laws that limit actions in a particular case); or
We are otherwise required or permitted to keep your information by applicable laws or regulations.
Where information is used for more than one purpose, we will retain it until the purpose with the latest period expires. For more information about our retention policies, please contact us using the contact details below.
California Personal Information Rights
If you are a California consumer, your rights regarding your Personal Information are set forth in more detail below.
Please note that if you submit a request to delete, request to know, or request to correct, Pure Flix will need to take reasonable steps to verify your identity before the request will be processed. To submit a request, you can click
here
. If you would like to opt out of sale of Personal Information or sharing of Personal Information for cross-contextual behavioral advertising please see instructions
here
. You may designate an authorized agent to make a request on your behalf; however, you will still need to verify your identity directly with us before your request can be processed. An authorized agent may submit a request on your behalf using the webform or toll-free number listed above.
The Right to Delete.
As a California resident you have the right to request Pure Flix to delete Personal Information which Pure Flix has collected from you, subject to certain exceptions.
Right to Correct Inaccurate Information.
If you believe that Personal Information we maintain about you is inaccurate, you have the right to request that we correct that information.
The Right to Know.
You have the right to know what Personal Information we have collected about you, which includes:
a. The categories of Personal Information we have collected about you, including
i. The categories of sources from which the Personal Information was collected
ii. Our business or commercial purposes for collecting, selling, or sharing Personal Information
iii. The categories of recipients to which we disclose Personal Information.
iv. The categories of Personal Information that we sold, and for each category identified, the categories of third parties to which we sold that particular category of Personal Information
v. The categories of Personal Information that we disclosed for a business purpose, and for each category identified, the categories of recipients to which we disclosed that particular category of Personal Information
b. The specific pieces of Personal Information we have collected about you.
Right to Opt Out of the Sale of Personal Information and Sharing of Personal Information for Cross-Contextual Behavioral Advertising.
California residents have the right to opt out of the sale of their Personal Information and sharing of Personal Information for cross-contextual behavioral advertising. To submit such a request, please click
here
. If you would like to opt out of sale of your Personal Information and sharing of Personal Information for cross contextual behavioral advertising for Tracking Technologies, including cookies and pixels, you will need to opt out of cookies by using the “
Manage Cookie Preferences
Tool” for each Pure Flix website you visit. We also accept certain opt-out preference signals sent from your browser that will opt you out of the sale and sharing of your Personal Information. Depending on how you have interacted with our services and our ability to identify you, this may only opt you out of sales and sharing that take place via cookies .
Right to Limit Use and Disclosure of Sensitive Personal Information.
You have the right to limit our use and disclosure of Sensitive Personal Information to uses that are reasonably necessary to perform services, provide goods to you, or as otherwise permitted by CCPA.
Right to Non-Discrimination.
A California consumer has the right not to receive discriminatory treatment by a business for the exercise of their privacy rights conferred by the CCPA.
Please note that if you make a privacy rights request, we will retain the Personal Data submitted in connection with your request for recordkeeping purposes.
